        <mxCell id="ext_note" value="&lt;font style='font-size:10px'&gt;&lt;b&gt;Architecture notes&lt;/b&gt;: Provisioning owns writes and persistence. Policy is synchronous on protected writes. Graph and Vector are eventually consistent read-optimized projections. Intelligence is read-only and composes SQL, Neo4j, and vector results. Budget, approval policy, purchase request, and budget-change logic currently live inside the Provisioning service, not as a separate microservice.&lt;/font&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#FFFDE7;strokeColor=#F9A825;fontSize=10;arcSize=8;" vertex="1" parent="1">
